9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1024, L.D. 1566, “An Act to Provide
10 Compensation to Individuals with Lived Experience Serving on Advisory Boards,
11 Commissions, Councils and Similar Groups”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Provide Compensation to Individuals with Lived Experience Serving on
14 Certain Advisory Boards, Commissions, Councils and Similar Groups'
15 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §12002, sub-§3-B is enacted to read:
17 3-B. Member representing lived experience. "Member representing lived
18 experience" means a board member serving on a board established in section 12004-I who
19 has first-hand knowledge or direct experience related to the content, subject matter,
20 responsibilities or authority of the board that helps increase equity in the representation of
21 perspectives and backgrounds of members; is not otherwise compensated for the member's
22 time serving on the board by the member's employer or the entity the member represents;
23 and is explicitly identified as a member representing lived experience in the statutory
24 language establishing the member's position as a member of a board.'
25 Amend the bill in section 3 in subsection 3 in the last line (page 1, line 28 in L.D.) by
26 inserting after the following: "board." the following: 'If the department or agency with
27 which the board is associated does not have sufficient money in the budget of the
28 department or agency to provide compensation and reimburse expenses, a member
29 representing lived experience or the board with which the member is associated may apply
30 for compensation pursuant to subsection 4.'
31 Amend the bill by inserting after section 3 the following:
32 'Sec. 4. 5 MRSA §12002-B, sub-§4 is enacted to read:
33 4. Lived experience funding; application for compensation. To the extent that
34 funding is available and appropriated by the Legislature for the purpose of providing
35 compensation to members with lived experience, a member or the board with which the
