5 Amend the bill by inserting after section 4 the following:
6 'Sec. 5. Lived experience funding distribution process developed by
7 Secretary of State. The Secretary of State shall develop a process for compensating
8 members of boards or commissions who are identified as members representing lived
9 experience as defined in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 12002, subsection 3-
10 B and as allowable under Title 5, section 12002-B, subsections 3 and 4. The process must
11 include the development of an application for members representing lived experience or
12 the board with which the member is associated to apply for compensation, the development
13 of a method of communication for any decisions to applicants who apply for compensation
14 and the development of policies or procedures governing the prioritization of compensation
15 requests. If no funding is available, the process is suspended.
16 Sec. 6. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
17 allocations are made.
18 SECRETARY OF STATE, DEPARTMENT OF
19 Bureau of Corporations, Elections and Commissions 0692
20 Initiative: Provides one-time funding to compensate individuals serving on boards and
21 commissions with lived experience.
