29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, changes the title of the
3311 bill and adds an appropriations and allocations section. It amends the bill by clarifying the
3322 definition of "member representing lived experience" to require that a board member serve
3333 on a board established in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 12004-I, that the
3344 board member is not otherwise compensated for the member's time serving on the board
3355 by the member's employer or the entity the member represents and that the board member
3366 representing lived experience be explicitly identified as such in the statutory language
3377 establishing the member's position as a member of a board.
3388 The amendment also allows the Secretary of State to provide compensation to members
3399 representing lived experience and provides a one-time General Fund allocation in fiscal
4400 year 2025-26 of $5,000. It also provides that if a department or agency of State
4411 Government with which a board is associated does not have sufficient money in the budget
4422 of the department or agency to provide compensation and reimburse expenses to members
